title: "Unreal Unearth"
creator: Hozier-Byrne, Andrew.

note: Album cover is a mouth surrounded dirt with a daisy in the mouth. Symbolizes being buried alive. Based/Inspired by Dante's Inferno.

title: "Enneagram"
creator: O'Neal, Ryan.
description: "Enneagram" is a complilation set from Sleeping at Last's eighth album.
note: "Enneagram" features 9 songs inspired by the 9 unique Enneagram personality types. The cover is black predominately with a gradient in the bottom left corner fading into white. "Enneagram" is in the center and the artist's name is underneath that.

title: "52nd Street"
location: New York City, New York, United States
creator: Joel, Billy.
description: "52nd Street" is the sixth studio album.
note: The title is a reference to 52nd Street in Midtown Manhattan as it was a popular spot for jazz musicians during the Great Depression. The cover is a photo of Joel holding a trumpet on 52nd Street in New York.

title: "The Stranger"
location: New York City, New York, United States
creator: Joel, Billy
description: "The Stranger" is the fifth studio album.
note: The cover features Joel sitting on a bed in a full suit with bare feet, and he is also sitting by a mask. This could symbolize Joel feeling out of place in his life and that he's had to put on a mask his entire life.

description: "Meliora" is the third studio album by Ghost.
note: The main theme of this album is the absence of God. The album cover takes inspiration from the theatrical release poster of the 1927 movie "Metropolis".

title: "Fine Line"
location: New York City, New York, United States
creator: Styles, Harry.
description: "Fine Line" is the second studio album by Harry Styles.
note: The album's themes revolve around breakups, happiness, sex, and sadness. The cover features Styles wearing an androgynous outfit, causing some to sspeculate that the title is in reference to Styles blurrring the lines of femininty and masculinity.

title: "Spirit Phone"
creator: Cicierega, Neil.
description: "Spirit Phone" is the seventth studio album and was originally self-released before Needlejuice Records re-released the album.
note: The cover art was created by Cicierega's wife, Ming Doyle, and is based off of a photo of Cicierega and the couple's cat.

description: "Atlas: Space" is a compilation album from Sleeping at Last.

title: "Creatures of the Night"
creator: Stanley, Paul; Simmons, Gene; Frehley, Ace; Carr, Eric.
description: "Creatures of the Night" is Kiss's tenth studio album.
note: This album was dedicated to Neil Bogart (1943-1982), one of Kiss's earliest supporters and the founder of Casablanca Records.

title: "Alive II"
creator: Stanley, Paul; Simmons, Gene; Criss, Peter; Frehley, Ace.
description: "Alive II" is a concet tour album, following the "Love Gun" tour. The tour started in 1977 and ended in 1978. The album was predominately a US tour, but there were 5 concerts in Japan as well.
note: The setlist for this tour was exactly the same as the Love Gun tour, except for two songs. "King of the Night Time World" and "Let Me Go, Rock 'n' Roll" being the two differeing songs.

title: "Rock and Roll Over"
creator: Stanley, Paul; Simmons, Gene; Criss, Peter; Frehley, Ace.
description: "Rock and Roll Over is Kiss's fifth studio album. It was recieved well for the most part,
